commit.message: Switched broken pypip.in badges to shields.io
A previous borked release means that there is a 0.2.dev14.. version in pypi, so this release is merely to have a stable version there instead
Applying the not-zip-safe flag to work around import problems when pylint loads the plugin via imp.find_module after using python setup.py install to install the package
Tidying up a couple of errors pointed out by Landscape

This takes care of the warning in a senario where
a task object is used without the decorator
syntax.
